    "text": "Mutagenesis studies showed that the HMA domain is indispensable for Cd binding. Deleting the HMA domain drastically reduced Cd accumulation and impaired yeast growth. Truncating other domains, such as the isoprenylation motif, had no significant effect. SbHIPP40 is a pivotal Cd accumulator via its HMA domain. This advances understanding of sorghum's Cd detoxification mechanisms and offers a genetic resource for enhancing phytoremediation strategies.",
